      <amcr:chranene_udaje>
        <amcr:lokalizace_okolnosti>The spa area in the JV part of the municipality, the Palliardi spring, south of the Imperial Spa building. Incentive: modification of a spring.</amcr:lokalizace_okolnosti>
        <amcr:souhrn_upresneni>A wooden structure was revealed when the spring was modified. Subsequent archaeological research has uncovered traces of hazing and multiple levels with remnants of treated and untreated wood, wooden structures, larger quantities of vegetable macro-residues (pine cones, hazelnuts), several pieces of chipped industrial, dated to the mezolite, and fragments of ceramic vessels dated to similar dustbins and the Bronze Age. The author of the research interpreted the remains of the wooden structure as the construction of a lighter cube from the late Bronze Age.
Several independent naturalistic analyses have provided information on the shape of the surrounding landscape. The research was complicated by high levels of groundwater or mineral springs. Much of the wood elements were degraded during preservation in the laboratory.</amcr:souhrn_upresneni>
      </amcr:chranene_udaje>
